passages.text: August 29, 2025 08:00 PM GMT
8x8 Inc (EGHT.O) Rating
Effective immediately, we are discontinuing coverage of 8x8 Inc (EGHT) due to a reallocation of resources. All prior research on EGHT should no longer be relied upon.

Our final rating is Equal- weight with a PT of \(\) 1.90\(. We are changing our final rating to EW (from UW) given encouraging signs of underlying stabilization at EGHT, from accelerating ex - Fuze growth and improved capital structure. Our reservation on EGHT has been that it will be multiple years until entire business growing at high single digits and we believe investments to pursue growth across FY26 will cause declining margins. Our PT of\) \ \(1.90\) represents \(\sim 8x\) FY27e FCF of \(\sim\) 70mm, remaining at a discount to SaaS comparables given competitive pressures in UCaaS and idiosyncratic headwinds (e.g. Fuze customer migration / churn). Our Bull case remains \(\) 3.90\(and represents \sim 9.5x FY26e bull case FCF of \sim\) 90mm, and assumes growth reaccelerates to mid- single digits. Our bear case remains \(\) 0.70\(and represents \sim 7x FY27e bear case FCF of \sim\) 55mm, which assumes cash flow generation diminishes and leverage levels can't be reduced. Risks to the upside include stronger ramp in new products, resiliency in UCaaS ARPU and M&A / consolidation in the space.

Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research
Secular Growth: Positive Self- help: Positive View descriptions of Risk Rewards Themes here

EGHT finds focus on CCaaS upsell. 8x8 can see some growth in low single digits as CCaaS and other new products find broader traction, which help to offset near term macro headwinds, and moves through Fuze migration/churn. Macro resolves ahead of expectations. Continues to trade at a discount given FCF margins, but more in- line with communication software peers. Using \~9.5x FY27e Bull Case FCF.

Struggle to get back to growth. Growth rates continue to be challenged and view prospects of getting back to mid- single digit growth challenging as UCaaS renewals come in at lower price points. Churn increases given macro, unable to be fully offset by newer products. Work to deliver, but free cash flow margins lag peers. Using \~8x FY27e Base Case FCF.

Execution challenges persist, does not resume organic growth. Go to market investments and management changes fail to materialize in significant change in trajectory and profitability lingers near breakeven. Struggles to show incremental profitability, turn around story falls out of favor with investors. Using \~7x FY27e bear case FCF.
